This is a **very important React concept**.

Iâ€™ll explain in your favorite style â†’ **step-by-step flow only**.

---

# âœ… What Does â€œPassing Function as Propâ€ Mean?

ğŸ‘‰ Parent component has a function
ğŸ‘‰ Parent sends that function to Child
ğŸ‘‰ Child calls that function

This is how **child talks to parent**.

---

# ğŸ§  Big Picture Flow

```
Parent
   â†“ (passes function)
Child
   â†“ (calls function)
Parent function runs
   â†“
State updates
```

---

# âœ… Step 1: Parent Component

```jsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import Child from "./Child";

function Parent() {

  const [message, setMessage] = useState("Hello");

  function changeMessage() {
    setMessage("Button Clicked ğŸš€");
  }

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>{message}</h2>

      <Child onButtonClick={changeMessage} />

    </div>
  );
}

export default Parent;
```

---

# âœ… Step 2: Child Component

```jsx
import React from "react";

function Child(props) {

  return (
    <button onClick={props.onButtonClick}>
      Click Me
    </button>
  );
}

export default Child;
```

---

# ğŸ”¥ What Is Happening?

### Step-by-step:

```
1ï¸âƒ£ Parent creates function changeMessage()
2ï¸âƒ£ Parent passes it as prop â†’ onButtonClick
3ï¸âƒ£ Child receives it in props
4ï¸âƒ£ Button click triggers props.onButtonClick()
5ï¸âƒ£ Parent function runs
6ï¸âƒ£ State updates
7ï¸âƒ£ Parent re-renders
```

---

# ğŸ¯ Why This Is Important?

Because:

ğŸ‘‰ Data flows **down** (parent â†’ child)
ğŸ‘‰ Events flow **up** (child â†’ parent)

This pattern is called:

> ğŸ”¥ "Lifting State Up"

---

# âœ… Passing Parameter from Child to Parent

Now advanced version ğŸ‘‡

---

### Parent

```jsx
